comment.author: 27331537@N06
comment._content: Paul, what a great idea! I found this on Wikipedia "...From 1910 to 1937, number plates [in New South Wales] were in numerals only. Prior to 1924, these were issued with black lettering on a white background, until recalled and subsequently replaced with the reverse colour format: white lettering on a black background. ...In 1937, letters in numberplates were first introduced..." The number plates in this image are white on black and numeric only - so can we assume the date is between 1924 and 1937? ps. Paul, I've copied some of this info over onto the blog post. AB

comment.author: 27331537@N06
comment._content: We have a c.1930s date thanks to our blog readers at Archives Outside. I think we now know more about the history of Australian car number plates that we thought possible!
